In [ ]:
for i in range(sims):
                returns_matrix[:,i] = np.random.normal(size=T, loc=daily_mean, scale=daily_volatility)
                prices_matrix[:,i] = np.cumprod(1 + returns_matrix[:,i]) * starting_price
In [ ]:
confidence_level = 0.05
            var = np.percentile(prices_matrix, confidence_level * 100)

VaR measures the maximum potential loss an investment portfolio is likely to face over a specified period for a given confidence interval. It provides a single, summary statistic for the risk of the portfolio.

In [ ]:
cvar = np.mean(prices_matrix[prices_matrix <= var])

CVaR is an extension of VaR that measures the expected loss of the portfolio given that the loss is greater than the VaR threshold. It provides a measure of the expected loss in the tail of the distribution (the worst-case scenario).
